20were%20able%20to%20cut%20many%20of%20Russia's%20routes%20into%20the%20fight.%20But%20then%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20weren't%20able%20to%20do%20it%20anymore.%20We%20didn't%20have%20the%20shells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20unit's%20reconnaissance%20team%20would%20report%20back%20to%20him%20to%20say%20they%20were%20able%20to%20see%20Russian%20trucks%20of%20shells%20arriving%20in%20Avdiivka%20and%20expected%20their%20information%20to%20result%20in%20Ukraine%20hitting%20those%20targets.%20But%20Ukraine%20didn't%20have%20the%20ammunition%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20photo%20of%20a%20snowy%20field%20with%20traces%20of%20artillery%20and%20recently%20destroyed%20Russian%20heavy%20equipment%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6613e6a016bde8d4ead66e63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20snowy%20field%20with%20traces%20of%20artillery%20and%20recently%20destroyed%20Russian%20heavy%20equipment%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Avdiivka%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20January%202024.%3Cp%3ELibkos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20Ukraine%20could%20no%20longer%20employ%20a%20key%20tactic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20big%20part%20of%20our%20tactical%20fight%20is%20suppressing%20these%20movements%20and%20logistics%20routes%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackie%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20it%20and%20we%20had%20it%20locked%2C%20and%20then%20we%20didn't%20%5Bhit%20it%5D%20because%20we%20ran%20our%20shells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20regularly%20been%20outnumbered%20in%20this%20fight%2C%20and%20many%20units%20have%20frequently%20been%20outgunned%2C%20facing%20a%20Russia%20that%20overpowers%20them%20in%20ammunition%20and%20manpower.%20That%20situation%20is%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20prevalent%20for%20Kyiv's%20forces%20as%20time%20goes%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUkraine%20was%20fighting%20better%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20odds%20stacked%20against%20it%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20able%20to%20stop%20Russia%20from%20taking%20over%20the%20country%20and%20from%20making%20significant%20progress%20in%20the%20east%20after%20pushing%20it%20back%20there.%20Many%20warfare%20experts%20have%20credited%20these%20successes%20to%20Ukraine's%20military%20making%20smarter%20tactical%20decisions%20with%20better-trained%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackie%20said%20Ukrainian%20advantages%20in%20training%2C%20tactics%2C%20and%20doctrine%20meant%20they%20outperformed%20the%20Russians%2C%20even%20in%20Avdiivka.%20He%20said%20that%20in%20the%20weeks%20running%20up%20to%20the%20withdrawal%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Russian%20units%20were%20getting%20creamed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20Russian%20tactics%20there%20as%20nonsensical%2C%20saying%20they%20%26quot%3Bwere%20a%20mess%2C%26quot%3B%20arguing%20that%20despite%20their%20weaponry%20advantage%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Russians%20miss%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20helps%20dull%20that%20edge.%20Ukraine%2C%20he%20said%2C%20has%20to%20be%20more%20accurate%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20its%20weaponry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20instructor%20with%20the%20military%2C%20Jackie%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20fighting%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20Ukraine.%20With%20Avdiivka%2C%20he%20went%20close%20to%20the%20town%20but%20did%20not%20go%20to%20the%20front%20line%2C%20instead%20collecting%20testimony%20from%20his%20unit%20to%20aid%20future%20tactics%20and%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20his%20men%20%26quot%3Bdestroyed%20two%20brigades%20worth%20of%20combat%20troops%20who%20were%20just%20throwing%20their%20guys%20at%20us%20basically%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20Ukraine's%20defense%20was%20ultimately%20unsustainable.%20His%20men%20also%20kept%20a%20corridor%20open%20for%20Ukrainian%20troops%20to%20retreat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222166%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20video%20appears%20to%20show%20a%20Russian%20soldier%20being%20struck%20by%20a%20Ukrainian%20drone%20in%20Avdiivka.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bcedaf6fcb546d2d4b7e28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221214%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDestruction%20in%20Avdiivka.%3Cp%3EKhorne%20Group%2FTelegram%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20said%20in%20February%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-losses-avdiivka-exceed-10-year-soviet-afghan-war-isw-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20Russian%20soldiers%20likely%20died%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20seize%20Avdiivka%20than%20died%20in%20the%20entire%20Soviet-Afghan%20war%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20conflict%20in%20which%20as%20many%20as%2025%2C000%20were%20estimated%20to%20have%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackie%20said%20%26quot%3Bwe%20really%20do%20not%20lose%20nearly%20as%20many%20guys%20as%20the%20Russians.%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20for%20sure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20it%20as%20worse%20for%20Russia%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbakhmut-how-ukraine-lost-city-russia-won-hollow-victory-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBakhmut%2C%20an%20eastern%20city%20that%20was%20the%20scene%20of%20what%20was%20long%20considered%20the%20bloodiest%20and%20most%20gruelling%20fight%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ukraine%20still%20had%20to%20leave%20Avdiivka.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20forces%20there%20outnumbered%20Ukrainian%20troops%20by%20seven%20to%20one%20and%20Russia%20launched%20up%20to%2060%20guided%20aerial%20bombs%20a%20day%20while%20Ukraine%20struggled%20with%20a%20lack%20of%20critical%20counter-air%20capabilities%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2F02%2F21%2Favdiivka-retreat-casualties-ukraine-russia%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20