n%20and%20women%20work%20from%20home%20at%20very%20similar%20rates%2C%20but%20there's%20some%20evidence%20that%20remote%20work%20is%20even%20more%20prevalent%20among%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aeaweb.org%2Fdoi%2Fpdfplus%2F10.1257%2Fjep.37.4.23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20Stanford%20economist%20Nicholas%20Bloom%20found%20that%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023%2C%20US%20women%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2020%20and%2064%20worked%20from%20home%20on%20roughly%2029%25%20of%20paid%20workdays%2C%20compared%20to%2027%25%20of%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20even%20evidence%20that%20suggests%20remote-working%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20men%20to%20take%20on%20extra%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20analysis%20of%202022%20and%202023%20Current%20Population%20Survey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcps.ipums.org%2Fcps%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20provided%20to%20Business%20Insider%20by%20Sarah%20Small%2C%20an%20assistant%20economics%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Utah%2C%20Small%20calculated%20that%2C%20among%20full%20or%20hybrid%20remote%20workers%2C%20roughly%207.8%25%20of%20women%20and%207.2%25%20of%20men%20reported%20working%20more%20than%20one%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Small%20said%20she%20was%20unable%20to%20determine%20whether%20these%20workers%20had%20two%20full-time%20roles%20and%20whether%20both%20were%20remote.%20It's%20possible%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20many%20of%20these%20women%20had%20a%20remote%20job%20and%20a%20part-time%2C%20non-remote%20second%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20February%2C%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20estimated%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FLNU02026631%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E386%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eless%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCLF16OV%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20were%20working%20two%20full-time%20jobs%20simultaneously%2C%20but%20it's%20uncertain%20what%20share%20of%20these%20people%20had%20two%20remote%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFewer%20women%20are%20overemployed%20because%20they're%20underrepresented%20in%20tech%20roles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20millennial%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-worker-woman-secretly-works-two-jobs-tech-millennial-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20she's%20on%20track%20to%20make%20nearly%20%24100%2C000%20in%20combined%20income%20this%20year%20across%20two%20remote%20program%20manager%20jobs%2C%20said%20she%20thinks%20there%20are%20significantly%20fewer%20overemployed%20women%20than%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20top%20theory%20to%20explain%20this%3A%20women%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmale-jobs-women-underrepresented-numbers-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderrepresented%20in%20tech%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20see%20tech%20as%20the%20main%20sector%20for%20overemployment%2C%20which%20is%20a%20field%20dominated%20by%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nicole%2C%20whose%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20BI%20but%20has%20been%20withheld%20due%20to%20her%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20female%20and%20non-tech%20and%20figured%20that%20was%20why%20I%20had%20less%20success%20securing%20job%20two.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20it%20took%20her%20nearly%20a%20year%20to%20find%20a%20second%20job%2C%20which%20was%20a%20part-time%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20women%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.womentech.net%2Fen-us%2Fwomen-in-tech-stats%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E35%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20tech%20employment%20in%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20WomenTech%20Network%2C%20a%20global%20organization%20that%20strives%20to%20increase%20diversity%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%20While%20some%20tech%20companies%20have%20called%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-ceos-remote-work-office-careers-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eback%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20have%20allowed%20employees%20to%20continue%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-typical-remote-worker-income-profession-age-2023-9%23they-earn-more-are-more-educated-and-are-more-likely-to-work-in-tech-or-similar-industries-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20remotely%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20providing%20them%20an%20opportunity%20to%20take%20on%20a%20second%20or%20third%20job%20if%20they%20wanted.%20As%20of%20last%20fall%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-from-home-return-to-office-americans-employment-wfh-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroughly%20a%20quarter%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20households%20had%20at%20least%20one%20person%20working%20remotely%20at%20least%20one%20day%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20more%20male-heavy%20fields%20like%20tech%20and%20finance%20have%20very%20high%20WFH%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20Stanford's%20Bloom%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20said%20tech%20roles%20are%20one%20of%20the%20few%20professions%20that%20have%20the%20combination%20of%20remote%20working%20arrangements%20and%20flexible%20hours%20that%20are%20often%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enecessary%20to%20pursue%20and%20sustain%20overemployment.%20Many%20of%20the%20job%20jugglers%20Business%20Insider%20has%20interviewed%20have%20worked%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-jobs-workers-millennials-tech-overemployment-retirement-savings-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20and%20IT%20industries%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20easy%20for%20people%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20tech%20people%20%E2%80%94%20to%20work%20multiple%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Wall%20Street%20forecaster%20Meredith%20Whitney%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-secret-jobs-economy-layoffs-unemployment-rate-meredith-whitney-2024-3%3Fr%3Drr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20that's%20what%20they've%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDifferences%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-childcare-costs-in-us-women-workforce-cheapest-countries-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20roles%20and%20expectations%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20also%20be%20dissuading%20some%20women%20from%20job%20juggling.%20In%202019%2C%20US%20women%20performed%2078%25%20of%20unpaid%20household%20production%20like%20childcare%2C%20laundry%2C%20and%20cooking%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Labor%20Department-commissioned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fcex%2Fconsumption%2Fintegrating-nonmarket-consumption-bls-consumer-expenditure-survey.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20economists%20at%20Bard%20College.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BData%20certainly%20suggest%20working%20mothers%20have%20less%20leisure%20time%20than%20working%20fathers%20and%20that%20working%20mothers%20spend%20much%20more%20time%20on%20housework%20and%20care%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Utah's%20Small%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20widespread%20remote%20work%20would%20make%20it%20possible%20for%20more%20women%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20there%20are%20still%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esome%20hurdles%20to%20equality%20in%20pay%2C%20Small%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20remote%20work%20alone%20isn't%20enough%20to%20help%20close%20gender%20gaps%2C%26quot%3B%2