nonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-news-futures-cpi-inflation-tsmc-ai-fed-rates-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Landlords%20have%20a%20secret%20weapon%20in%20the%20war%20over%20high%20rents%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22How%20landlords%20use%20algorithms%20to%20jack%20up%20your%20rent.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615b1a216bde8d4ead73180%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBig-time%20apartment%20owners%20have%20a%20secret%20weapon%3A%20a%20software%20that%20helps%20property%20managers%20to%20help%20them%20set%20rents%20and%20juice%20their%20profits%3Cp%3EEmrah_Oztas%2F%20Getty%20Image%2C%20eGreg%20Bajor%2FGetty%20Image%2C%20Aleksey%20Balatskiy%2FGetty%20Image%2C%20Cici%20Morosanu%2F500px%2FGetty%20Image%2C%20Bus%C3%A0%20Photography%2FGetty%20Image%2C%20Abanti%20Chowdhury%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELandlords%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20built-in%20leverage%20over%20renters.%20Moving%20is%20a%20pain%2C%20so%20tenants%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20accept%20rent%20hikes.%20Developing%20new%20apartments%20is%20expensive%20and%20time-consuming%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20tough%20for%20competitors%20to%20enter%20the%20market.%20Even%20during%20shaky%20periods%20for%20the%20economy%2C%20rents%20tend%20to%20hold%20steady%20or%20even%20climb%20%E2%80%94%20people%20still%20need%20to%20live%20somewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20the%20playing%20field%20tilted%20further%20in%20favor%20of%20landlords.%20Rents%20soared%20thanks%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-inequality-housing-shortage-causes-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshortage%20of%20apartment%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20remote%20workers'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-apartment-rent-high-pandemic-big-cities-household-formation-roommates-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edesire%20for%20more%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20daunting%20for-sale%20market%20that%20kept%20many%20renters%20stuck%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig-time%20apartment%20owners%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20also%20had%20a%20secret%20weapon%3A%20a%20Texas%20company%20called%20RealPage%2C%20which%20sells%20software%20to%20property%20managers%20to%20help%20them%20set%20rents%20and%20juice%20their%20profits.%20Its%20algorithm%20tells%20landlords%20exactly%20how%20much%20rent%20they%20should%20charge%20for%20units%20in%20their%20buildings%2C%20based%20on%20a%20potent%20mix%20of%20both%20public%20and%20nonpublic%20data%20that%20property%20owners%20supply%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERealPage%20openly%20brags%20about%20its%20ability%20to%20help%20clients%20%26quot%3Boutpace%20the%20market%20in%20good%20times%20and%20bad.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20new%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20company%2C%20Kris%20Mayes%2C%20Arizona's%20attorney%20general%2C%20offered%20a%20translation%3A%20%26quot%3B'Outpace'%20is%20code%20for%20charging%20higher%20prices%20than%20what%20would%20be%20charged%20in%20a%20market%20untainted%20by%20collusion%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%20reads.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20price%20fixing%2C%20and%20it%20is%20illegal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20is%20one%20of%20dozens%20that%20accuse%20RealPage%20of%20operating%20a%20vast%20conspiracy%20to%20overcharge%20renters%20via%20its%20prized%20algorithm.%20Critics%20say%20the%20cooperation%20between%20RealPage%20and%20apartment%20managers%20has%20emboldened%20landlords%20to%20raise%20prices%20even%20if%20it%20means%20more%20units%20are%20left%20empty%20when%20tenants%20are%20forced%20to%20leave.%20Without%20RealPage%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20argue%2C%20landlords%20would%20be%20hesitant%20to%20jack%20up%20rents%3B%20instead%2C%20they'd%20focus%20on%20keeping%20their%20buildings%20full.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cases%20offer%20a%20revealing%20glimpse%20at%20how%20corporate%20apartment%20owners%20rely%20on%20technology%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F12-million-americans-spend-over-half-paycheck-rent-harvard-study-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewring%20every%20last%20dollar%20out%20of%20tenants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20often%20have%20little%20idea%20how%20their%20rents%20are%20calculated%20or%20why%20a%20double-digit%20annual%20percentage%20increase%20is%20justified.%20But%20a%20win%20for%20the%20plaintiffs%20is%20far%20from%20guaranteed.%20Without%20hard%20evidence%20of%20shady%20dealings%20in%20a%20smoke-filled%20backroom%2C%20they'll%20likely%20have%20to%20prove%20that%20use%20of%20the%20algorithm%2C%20and%20the%20cooperation%20it%20facilitated%20among%20apartment-owning%20competitors%2C%20unfairly%20pushed%20up%20prices%20and%20ultimately%20did%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20plaintiffs%20succeed%2C%20though%2C%20the%20ripple%20effects%20could%20extend%20well%20beyond%20rental%20housing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-helping-retailers-stores-predictive-dynamic-pricing-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlgorithmic%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bdynamic%2C%26quot%3B%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20used%20in%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20industries%2C%20including%20hospitality%2C%20retail%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20entertainment.%20These%20cases%20could%20provide%20a%20road%20map%20for%20class-action%20lawyers%20to%20target%20those%20sectors%2C%20too.%20In%20short%2C%20the%20lawsuits%20that%20started%20with%20apartment%20rents%20could%20one%20day%20change%20how%20we%20pay%20for%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ERealPage%20may%20not%20be%20a%20household%20name%2C%20but%20if%20you%20live%20in%20a%20major%20US%20city%2C%20you've%20probably%20walked%20past%20(or%20lived%20in)%20an%20apartment%20that%20had%20its%20rent%20price%20set%20by%20the%20software.%20Its%20clients%2C%20as%20of%202020%2C%20the%20last%20year%20data%20was%20publicly%20available%2C%20included%20the%2010%20largest%20multifamily%20property-management%20companies%20in%20the%20US.%20Its%20suite%20of%20services%20is%20used%20to%20manage%20more%20than%2024%20million%20units%20worldwide%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company's%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERealPage%20wields%20the%20greatest%20power%20in%20markets%20with%20a%20high%20concentration%20of%20corporate-owned%20apartments.%20About%2070%25%20of%20apartment%20units%20in%20the%20Phoenix%20metropolitan%20area%20are%20owned%20or%20managed%20by%20companies%20that%20use%20RealPage%20for%20%26quot%3Brevenue%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20term%20for%20the%20price-recommendation%20software%20that%20is%20now%20under%20scrutiny%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20by%20Arizona's%20attorney%20general.%20In%20Tucson%2C%20about%20half%20of%20listed%20apartments%20fall%20under%20that%20umbrella.%20The%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20attorney%20general%2C%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-apartment-rent-price-setting-landlords-realpage-lawsuit-illegal-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20sued%20RealPage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20that%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20multifamily%20units%20in%20the%20district%2C%20and%2060%25%20of%20units%20in%20buildings%20with%2050%20or%20more%20units%2C%20were%20priced%20using%20RealPage's%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERealPage%20and%20its%20executives%20aren't%20shy%20about%20touting%20the%20benefits%20of%20its%20algorithm%20for%20landlords.%20A%20video%20on%20its%20website%20heralds%20the%20software%2C%20known%20simply%20as%20%26quot%3BAI%20Revenue%20Management%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20pricing-optimization%20tool%20to%20fully%20employ%20AI%20and%20machine%20learning%2C%26quot%3B%20helping%20properties%20%26quot%3Bexceed%20the%20market%20by%202%25%20to%205%25.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20company's%20clients%20enjoy%20revenue%20increases%20from%20year%20to%20year%20that%20are%20greater%20than%20the%20market%20average.%20RealPage's%20algorithm%20is%20fueled%20by%20troves%20of%20granular%20data%20on%20real-time%20lease%20transactions%2C%20occupancy%2C%20and%20how%20many%20units%20are%20hitting%20the%20market%2C%20which%20landlords%20feed%20the%20company%20as%20a%20condition%20of%20using%20its%20services.%20It's%20unclear%20exactly%20how%20the%20company%20massages%20all%20those%20numbers%20to%20spit%20out%20its%20price%20recommendations%2C%20but%20RealPage%20says%20it%20aggregates%20and%20anonymizes%20the%20data%20from%20other%20apartment%20operators%20in%20the%20area%20and%20combines%20it%20with%20other%20public%20data%20and%20the%20property's%20internal%20rent%20data%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20suggested%20dollar%20amount.%20It's%20%26quot%3Bboth%20common%20and%20expected%26quot%3B%20that%20apartment%20managers%20will%20follow%20the%20system's%20pricing%20recommendations%20on%20roughly%2080%25%20to%2095%25%20of%20their%20decisions%2C%20RealPage's%20website%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20turning%20over%20pricing%20to%20the%20algorithm%2C%20plaintiffs%20say%2C%20RealPage's%20clients%20are%20encouraged%20to%20push%20rents%20higher%20than%20if%20they'd%20left%20the%20decisions%20up%20to%20humans.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20take%20their%20word%20for%20it%2C%20though%20%E2%80%94%20both%20the%20company%20and%20its%20users%20have%20publicly%20hailed%20the%20software's%20ability%20to%20capture%20more%20revenue.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20property%20manager%2C%20very%20few%20of%20us%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20actually%20raise%20rents%20double%20digits%20within%20a%20single%20month%20by%20doing%20it%20manually%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20RealPage%20executive%20said%20in%20a%20since%20deleted%20video%2C%20according%20to%20a%202022%20investigation%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fyieldstar-rent-increase-realpage-rent%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProPublica%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Another%20apartment%20manager%20said%20in%20a%20testimonial%20video%20that%20the%20software%20%26quot%3Bpushes%20you%20to%20go%20places%20that%20you%20wouldn't%20have%20gone%20if%20you%20weren't%20using%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-homes-apartments-low-rent-scarce-expensive-housing-real-estate-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERental%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20shot%20up%20by%2029.4%25%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20averaging%20an%20annual%20increase%20of%207%25%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%20Zillow%20found.%20Almost%20two-thirds%20of%20that%20increase%20happened%20in%202021%20alone%2C%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20pandemic-era%20housing%20market.%20Of%20course%2C%20there%20were%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-apartment-rent-high-pandemic-big-cities-household-formation-roommates-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efactors%20driving%20up%20rents%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20then%20that%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20algorithms%2C%20most%20notably%20an%20increase%20in%20household%20formation%20%E2%80%94%20people%20broke%20up%20with%20their%20roommates%2C%20moved%20out%20of%20their%20parents'%20houses%2C%20or%20simply%20upgraded%20to%20more%20space%20%E2%80%94%20so%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20exactly%20how%20much%20to%20ascribe%20to%20the%20algorithms.%20But%20information%20asymmetry%20is%20part%20of%20the%20bigger%20problem.%20Apartment%20owners%20have%20access%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20market%20data%20through%20RealPage's%20algorithm%2C%20while%20tenants%20suffer%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20information%20%E2%80%94%20some%20can't%20even%20figure%20out%20who%20actually%20owns%20their%20apartment%20behind%20a%20web%20of%20LLCs.%20The%20plaintiffs%20allege%20that%20RealPage%20clients%20provide%20data%20to%20the%20company%20knowing%20that%20many%20of%20their%20competitors%20are%20doing%20the%20same%20and%20that%20they%20would%20all%20benefit%20by%20participating.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20lawsuits%20claim%20that%20RealPage%20shares%20%26quot%3Bpeer%20lists%26quot%3B%20with%20clients%20that%20tell%20them%20exactly%20who%20else%20is%20providing%20data%20to%20the%20company%20within%20a%20specific%20distance%20of%20their%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20kinds%20of%20other%20issues%20crop%20up%20when%20landlords%20rely%20on%20algorithms%20instead%20of%20human%20expertise%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20say.%20At%20least%20when%20renters%20go%20back%20and%20forth%20with%20a%20real%20human%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-negotiate-rent-apartment-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elease%20negotiations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there's%20a%20chance%20they%20could%20bargain%20the%20price%20down%2C%20Marie%20Claire%20Tran-Leung%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Evictions%20Initiative%20Project%20at%20the%20National%20Housing%20Law%20Project%2C%20told%20me.%20An%20algorithm%20may%20not%20be%20so%20lenient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20takes%20the%20tenant%20out%20of%20the%20equation%20altogether%2C%26quot%3B%20Tran-Leung%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202009%20movie%20%26quot%3BThe%20Informant!%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Damon%20plays%20a%20bumbling%20white-collar%20worker%20who%20tips%20off%20the%20FBI%20that%20his%20company%20and%20its%20competitors%20are%20meeting%20to%20fix%20prices.%20The%20tale%20is%20based%20on%20a%20real-life%20case%20from%20the%20'90s%20that%20offered%20up%20a%20classic%20model%20of%20collusion%2C%20in%20which%20executives%20meet%20in%20secret%20and%20make%20handshake%20deals%20to%20screw%20over%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlgorithms%20aren't%20so%20straightforward.%20There%20are%20no%20smoky%20rooms%2C%20no%20opportunities%20for%20a%20wire-wearing%20whistleblower%20to%20catch%20the%20crooks%20red-handed.%20In%20a%20recent%20statement%20of%20interest%20in%20the%20lawsuits%20against%20RealPage%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20referred%20to%20algorithms%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bnew%20frontier%26quot%3B%20of%20price%20fixing%2C%20arguing%20that%20they%20posed%20%26quot%3Ban%20even%20greater%20anticompetitive%20threat%26quot%3B%20than%20anything%20that%20had%20come%20before.%20By%20sharing%20private%20information%20and%20surrendering%20their%20decision-making%20to%20the%20software%2C%20companies%20are%20engaging%20in%20price-fixing%20behavior%2C%20the%20department%20claimed.%20They%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20hold%20secret%20meetings%3B%20the%20algorithm%20does%20all%20the%20heavy%20lifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAutomating%20an%20anticompetitive%20scheme%20does%20not%20make%20it%20less%20anticompetitive%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department's%20statement%20said.%20In%202017%2C%20Maureen%20Ohlhausen%2C%20then%20a%20commissioner%20at%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%2C%20voiced%20similar%20concerns%20about%20pricing%20algorithms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverywhere%20the%20word%20'algorithm'%20appears%2C%20please%20just%20insert%20the%20words%20'a%20guy%20named%20Bob%2C'%26quot%3B%20Ohlhausen%20said.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20OK%20for%20a%20guy%20named%20Bob%20to%20collect%20confidential%20price-strategy%20information%20from%20all%20the%20participants%20in%20a%20market%2C%20and%20then%20tell%20everybody%20how%20they%20should%20price%3F%20If%20it%20isn't%20OK%20for%20a%20guy%20named%20Bob%20to%20do%20it%2C%20then%20it%20probably%20isn't%20OK%20for%20an%20algorithm%20to%20do%20it%2C%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20model%20of%20collusion%20is%20what%20experts%20call%20a%20%26quot%3Bhub-and-spoke%26quot%3B%20conspiracy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20plaintiffs%20will%20argue%20that%20RealPage%20is%20at%20the%20center%2C%20or%20the%20hub%2C%20and%20the%20arrangements%20with%20each%20of%20its%20clients%20are%20the%20spokes.%20The%20problem%20for%20the%20plaintiffs%20is%20they%20also%20need%20to%20show%20that%20there's%20a%20%3Cem%3Erim%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20this%20wheel%3A%20an%20agreement%20between%20all%20the%20competitors%20to%20use%20the%20algorithm%20and%20pump%20up%20their%20profits.%20That%20rim%20is%20pretty%20important%3B%20without%20it%2C%20the%20plaintiffs'%20case%20gets%20a%20lot%20more%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20CEOs%20get%20together%20and%20agree%20to%20push%20up%20prices%2C%20the%20mere%20act%20of%20doing%20so%20is%20illegal%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20they%20actually%20pull%20off%20the%20scheme.%20But%20with%20a%20rimless%20hub-and-spoke%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20have%20to%20prove%20that%20each%20of%20the%20agreements%20between%20RealPage%20and%20its%20clients%20stifles%20competition%20and%20harms%20consumers.%20That's%20a%20much%20higher%20standard%2C%20Ed%20Rogers%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Ballard%20Spahr%20who%20specializes%20in%20antitrust%20cases%2C%20told%20me.%20To%20avoid%20this%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20will%20try%20to%20establish%20that%20a%20rim%20does%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20exist%20%E2%80%94%20that%20apartment%20managers%20either%20agreed%20with%20one%20another%20to%20use%20RealPage%20to%20collectively%20raise%20prices%2C%20or%20at%20least%20used%20its%20software%20knowing%20and%20expecting%20that%20their%20competitors%20would%20do%20the%20same%20and%20that%20they%20would%20all%20benefit%20by%20participating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20to%20prove%20a%20conspiracy%20with%20circumstantial%20evidence%2C%20Jeffery%20Cross%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Smith%20Gambrell%20Russell%2C%20told%20me.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20court%20might%20look%20at%20whether%20apartment%20owners%20had%20strong%20incentives%20to%20collude%2C%20whether%20they%20knew%20who%20else%20was%20participating%2C%20whether%20participation%20was%20enforced%20in%20some%20way%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20all%20took%20similar%20actions%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20like%20raising%20prices%20in%20unison.%20The%20judge%20could%20also%20consider%20whether%20the%20competitors%20knew%20that%20the%20price%20increases%20could%20succeed%20only%20if%20everyone%20did%20the%20same.%20But%20proving%20a%20rim%20this%20way%20is%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20more%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Cross%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERealPage%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%2C%20but%20in%20a%20rebuttal%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20statement%20of%20interest%2C%20the%20company%20said%20it%20may%20recommend%20price%20%3Cem%3Edecreases%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20noted%20that%20apartment%20managers%20didn't%20always%20accept%20its%20suggestions.%20It%20also%20said%20there%20wasn't%20enough%20evidence%20to%20prove%20that%20the%20apartment%20managers%20had%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Bconscious%20commitment%26quot%3B%20to%20engage%20in%20an%20unlawful%20scheme%20together.%20In%20short%2C%20no%20rim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20RealPage%20is%20far%20from%20the%20only%20reason%20that%20rents%20rose%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20And%20because%20a%20ton%20of%20new%20apartment%20buildings%20were%20completed%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20rents%20around%20the%20country%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-decline-fall-apartment-housing-market-landlords-tenant-lease-construction-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estagnating%20or%20even%20dropping%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20some%20areas.%20But%20the%20plaintiffs%20in%20these%20cases%20still%20argue%20that%20the%20rental%20market%20would%20be%20better%20for%20tenants%20if%20RealPage%20didn't%20exist%3B%20if%20apartment%20owners%20couldn't%20lean%20on%20the%20algorithm%2C%20they%20might%20hold%20off%20on%20rent%20hikes%20or%20drop%20prices%20more%20frequently.%20They%20might%20also%20be%20more%20open%20to%20negotiating%20on%20lease%20renewals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20have%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20before%20knowing%20whether%20these%20changes%20will%20come%20to%20pass.%20The%20Justice%20Department%20has%20opened%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20into%20RealPage%20and%20some%20of%20its%20customers%2C%20Politico%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F03%2F20%2Frental-housing-market-doj-investigation-00147333%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20mounting%20pressure%20on%20the%20company%20and%20its%20clients.%20The%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20and%20Arizona%20attorneys%20general%20will%20work%20their%20way%20through%20their%20respective%20judicial%20systems%2C%20while%20the%20federal%20antitrust%20cases%20have%20been%20consolidated%20before%20a%20judge%20in%20Tennessee.%20The%20first%20of%20those%20cases%20was%20filed%20in%202022%2C%20so%20they're%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20%E2%80%94%20it%20could%20be%20years%20before%20we%20even%20see%20a%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20that%20day%20comes%2C%20it'll%20be%20worth%20watching.%20The%20RealPage%20cases%20are%20about%20far%20more%20than%20apartment%20rents.%20If%20the%20plaintiffs%20can%20successfully%20argue%20that%20property%20managers%20engaged%20in%20price%20fixing%20by%20using%20RealPage's%20algorithm%2C%20they%20could%20open%20the%20door%20for%20all%20kinds%20of%20industries%20to%20face%20similar%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-brought-skiplagging-upon-themselves-with-nonsense-pricing-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erely%20heavily%20on%20algorithms%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20price%20plane%20tickets%2C%20and%20experts%20have%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20industry%20is%20especially%20susceptible%20to%20collusion%20because%20it%20is%20dominated%20by%20just%20a%20handful%20of%20major%20players.%20The%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20has%20accused%20Amazon%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-used-secret-algorithm-raise-rival-site-prices-antitrust-lawsuit-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20a%20secret%20algorithm%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20see%20whether%20it%20could%20raise%20prices%20and%20prompt%20other%20businesses%20to%20follow%20suit.%20Just%20recently%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20and%20the%20FTC%20filed%20%3Cem%3Eanother%20%3C%2Fem%3Estatement%20of%20interest%20in%20a%20case%20that%20accuses%20casino-hotel%20operators%20of%20propping%20up%20prices%20by%20using%20a%20common%20algorithm.%20The%20platform%20in%20question%20is%20called%20Rainmaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapartment-rent-increases-landlords-antitrust-lawsuits-real-estate-software-realpage-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712741221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615b3123f923f7dab062836%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapartment-rent-increases-landlords-antitrust-lawsuits-real-estate-software-realpage-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prosecutors%20say%20a%20tech%20company%20is%20helping%20landlords%20work%20together%20to%20drive%20up%20rents.%20The%20lawsuit's%20outcome%20could%20change%20how%20we%20pay%20for%20everything.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jrodriguez%40insider.com%20(James%20Rodriguez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapartment-rent-increases-landlords-antitrust-lawsuits-real-estate-software-realpage-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20started%20an%20Etsy%20candle%20store%20last%20year.%20The%20passive%20income%20helped%20me%20move%20out%20of