%3Cp%3EIt's%20meant%20I%20could%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Bintermittent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-worker-promoted-senior-manager-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enomad%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I%20travel%20while%20running%20my%20business%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20away%20for%20super%20long%20periods%20of%20time%2C%20and%20I%20like%20having%20a%20home%20base%20to%20return%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20starting%20Etsy%2C%20I%20worked%20online%20and%20lived%20in%20Orlando%20with%20my%20parents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20I%20had%20to%20move%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregret-not-moving-chicago-texas-facebook-austin-dallas-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20home%20with%20my%20parents%20in%20Orlando.%20I%20was%20pretty%20desperate%20for%20work%2C%20and%20though%20I'd%20never%20pictured%20myself%20working%20with%20kids%2C%20I%20started%20working%20as%20a%20teacher%20for%20an%20online%20education%20platform%20called%20Outschool%2C%20teaching%20logic%20and%20critical%20thinking%20skills%20to%20kids%20online%20using%20the%20game%20Minecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20loving%20it.%20I%20liked%20being%20in%20charge%20of%20making%20a%20curriculum%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20like%20that%20my%20schedule%20was%20locked%20into%20specific%20teaching%20hours.%20I%20wanted%20more%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20looking%20for%20potential%20side%20hustles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20looking%20into%20other%20options%2C%20such%20as%20copywriting.%20I%20came%20across%20some%20TikToks%20from%20people%20selling%20via%20print-on-demand%20platforms%20in%20January%202023.%20I%20felt%20that%20was%20the%20best%20route.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20YouTube%20videos%2C%20sellers%20said%20T-shirts%20and%20mugs%20were%20quite%20saturated%20markets.%20It%20seemed%20as%20though%20the%20best%20approach%20was%20to%20choose%20one%20niche%20that%20could%20be%20applied%20to%20multiple%20products%20or%20one%20product%20that%20could%20be%20tailored%20to%20different%20niches%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20scoured%20Printify%2C%20a%20print-on-demand%20platform%2C%20and%20found%20they%20were%20offering%20candles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20some%20research%20into%20how%20well%20candles%20were%20selling%20on%20Etsy%20%E2%80%94%20it%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20space.%20They%20make%20good%20gifts%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20market%20for%20candles%20with%20funny%20messages%20where%20I%20could%20replace%20the%20text%20to%20apply%20to%20different%20niches.%20I%20saw%20shops%20that%20were%20successful%20in%20doing%20that%20over%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20research%20trending%20words%20or%20topics%20and%20come%20up%20with%20a%20joke%20or%20a%20cuss%20related%20to%20that%20trend%20for%20the%20candles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20considered%20handling%20my%20own%20inventory%2C%20but%20using%20a%20print-on-demand%20platform%20didn't%20require%20me%20to%20spend%20money%20upfront%20or%20stay%20in%20one%20location.%20It%20seemed%20like%20a%20no-brainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20Canva%20to%20experiment%20with%20different%20designs%20for%20the%20text%20printed%20on%20the%20candles%20and%20uploaded%20them%20onto%20Etsy.%20I%20landed%20on%20the%20most%20popular%20design%20and%20changed%20the%20text%20with%20different%20funny%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20meant%20each%20new%20product%20didn't%20need%20a%20new%20design%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20very%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manufacturing%20partner%20that%20Printify%20works%20with%20offers%2010%20different%20scents.%20Customers%20can%20choose%20which%20scent%20they%20want%20and%20pair%20it%20with%20a%20phrase.%20I%20also%20have%20an%20option%20for%20buyers%20to%20customize%20the%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20first%20couple%20of%20months%20were%20slow%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20a%20while%20to%20get%20people%20to%20trust%20you%20and%20to%20land%20reviews.%20I%20put%20out%20two%20or%20three%20products%20a%20day.%20I%20launched%20the%20shop%20in%20January%202023%20and%20by%20March%2C%20my%20sales%20were%20picking%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20wasn't%20a%20viable%20full-time%20income%20until%20December%20when%20sales%20went%20through%20the%20roof%20because%20of%20Christmas.%20I%20made%20%24136%2C700%20in%20revenue%20from%20November%20to%20December%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20realized%20my%20Etsy%20store%20could%20replace%20my%20income%20from%20teaching.%20I%20decided%20to%20quit%20in%20December%202023%20%E2%80%94%20I%20probably%20could%20have%20before%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20my%20store%20was%20viable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuitting%20my%20job%20was%20scary%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20that%20even%20if%20this%20particular%20shop%20failed%2C%20I%20could%20set%20up%20another%20store%20on%20Etsy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20spend%204%20hours%20at%20most%20a%20day%20on%20my%20store%20%E2%80%94%20and%20usually%20a%20lot%20less%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spend%20between%2020%20and%2030%20minutes%20a%20day%20on%20custom%20orders.%20I%20can%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20as%20I%20want%20uploading%20candles.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20spend%20around%20three%20or%20four%20hours%20a%20day%20on%20that%2C%20about%20one%20in%20every%20four%20working%20days.%20The%20rest%20is%20passive%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20go%20into%20maintain%20mode%20and%20just%20live%20life.%20I've%20spent%20the%20last%20two%20weeks%20in%20Bali.%20I've%20traveled%20to%20Belgium%2C%20France%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20the%20Caribbean%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20able%20to%20afford%20my%20own%20place%20in%20Orlando%20and%20travel%20when%20I%20want%20is%20a%20huge%20win.s%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetsy-store-move-out-parents-t