%3E%3Cli%3EDaniel%20Bennett%20is%20a%20self-proclaimed%C2%A0%26quot%3Bpersonality%20hire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20applying%20for%20his%20first%20job%2C%20he%20focused%20on%20making%20his%20interviewers%20like%20him%20rather%20than%20trying%20to%20impress%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPersonality%20hires%20are%20important%20for%20building%20company%20culture%2C%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Daniel%20Bennett%2C%20the%2028-year-old%20founder%20of%20DX%20Creative%2C%20a%20social%20consulting%20agency%2C%20and%20a%20former%20advertising%20account%20manager.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonality-hires-bring-soft-skills-to-work-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersonality%20hire%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20interviewing%20for%20my%20first%20corporate%20job%20at%20a%20giant%20advertising%20agency%20in%20LA%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ferin-riley-appointed-ceo-of-tbwa-chiat-day-united-states-1032819231%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETBWA%5C%5CChiat%5C%5CDay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20goal%20going%20into%20it%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-attractive-personality-traits-of-job-candidates-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20the%20interviewers%20like%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20was%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20there%20to%20impress%20them%20or%20show%20them%20that%20I%20could%20learn%20or%20whatever.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20can%20make%20them%20laugh%20and%20smile%20and%20have%20a%20good%20time%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20more%20memorable%20than%20someone%20who%20can%20recite%20all%20of%20their%20accolades.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it%20was%20an%20ad%20agency%20in%20LA%2C%20there%20was%20a%20basketball%20court%20in%20the%20office%2C%20and%20their%20first%20question%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BDid%20you%20see%20the%20basketball%20court%20behind%20you%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20opening%20line%20in%20the%20interview%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I%20was%20taking%20warmup%20shots%20for%20this%20interview%20before%20you%20guys%20came.%20Am%20I%20sweaty%3F%26quot%3B%20They%20loved%20that%3B%20they%20were%20laughing%20their%20asses%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20beating%20out%20two%20people%20with%20three%20or%20four%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20even%20though%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuilding-career-with-no-previous-work-experience-tips-strategy-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezero%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDifference%20between%20a%20personality%20hire%20and%20a%20good%20personality.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20difference%20between%20a%20personality%20hire%20and%20someone%20who%20just%20has%20a%20good%20personality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20walking%20into%20work%20with%20your%20coffee%2C%20and%20the%20personality%20hire%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20never%20going%20to%20guess%20who%20I%20ran%20into%20this%20weekend!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20normal%20person%20might%20keep%20that%20information%20to%20themselves%2C%20but%20a%20personality%20hire%20will%20want%20to%20entertain%20the%20office%20with%20their%20hilarious%20story%20of%20running%20into%20an%20ex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20can%20get%20away%20with%20doing%20less%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20personality%20hire%2C%20you%20can%20get%20away%20with%20not%20being%20as%20competent%20and%20doing%20half%20of%20your%20job.%20(I'm%20not%20that%20kind%20of%20person%2C%20but%20there%20are%20personality%20hires%20like%20that.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoes%20that%20mean%20that%20someone%20else%20picks%20up%20the%20slack%3F%20Probably.%20But%20that's%20up%20to%20the%20company's%20discretion%20to%20decide%20whether%20they%20keep%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20certain%20people%20who%20perhaps%20don't%20crush%20tests%20or%20can't%20build%20a%20marketing%20rollout%20but%20are%20very%20successful%20in%20their%20roles%20because%20they're%20street%20smart.%20Maybe%20a%20personality%20hire%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20connections%20and%20always%20%26quot%3Bknows%20a%20guy%26quot%3B%20who%20can%20get%20you%20into%20a%20restaurant%20that's%20booked%20out%20for%20six%20months%2C%20which%20could%20result%20in%20closing%20a%20deal.%20But%20maybe%20that%20person%20doesn't%20know%20how%20to%20write%20a%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20%26quot%3Bknow%20a%20guy%26quot%3B%20skills%20really%20come%20in%20handy%20with%20careers%20that%20are%20built%20around%20relationship%20management%2C%20which%20is%20more%20meaningful%20than%20being%20good%20at%20sending%20emails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20if%20you're%20just%20a%20personality%20hire%20and%20do%20absolutely%20no%20work%2C%20you%20will%20get%20fired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20a%20personality%20hire%2C%20I%20still%20worked%20hard%3B%20I%20worked%2060%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20was%20up%20until%201%20a.m.%20so%20we%20could%20finish%20a%20commercial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20instances%2C%20personality%20hires'%20positive%20attitudes%20help.%20Cracking%20jokes%20with%20your%20coworkers%20at%201%20a.m.%20on%20a%20deadline%20makes%20it%20much%20more%20bearable%20than%20everyone%20being%20miserable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20a%20personality%20hire%20allowed%20me%20to%20call%20in%20favors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20office%2C%20I%20was%20the%20one%20who%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BGuys%2C%20we%20have%20an%20hour%20in%20between%20meetings.%20Let's%20go%20walk%20and%20get%20lunch!%26quot%3B%20Or%20%26quot%3BLet's%20go%20grab%20a%20smoothie.%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20place%20is%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foffice-quiet-but-happy-hour-still-kicking-after-pandemic-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappy%20hour%20after%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Are%20you%20coming%3F%26quot%3B%20It's%20those%20little%20things%20that%20some%20companies%20would%20call%20team%20bonding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20low-level%20account%20assistant%2C%20I%20did%20all%20the%20grunt%20work%2C%20like%20organizing%20files%20and%20picking%20up%20hard%20drives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20was%20always%20good%20at%20walking%20around%20the%20office%20and%20talking%20to%20different%20people%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-new-coworkers-like-you-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20instead%20of%20sending%20a%20Slack%20message%20or%20an%20email%2C%20I%20would%20go%20up%20and%20ask%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20thought%20that%20if%20I%20need%20a%20favor%20from%20someone%2C%20they're%20way%20more%20likely%20to%20help%20me%20out%20if%20I've%20gone%20up%20to%20them%20and%20said%20hi%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20sent%20them%20an%20email%20and%20never%20talked%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20runs%20on%20favors%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20do%20favors%20for%20people%20that%20you%20don't%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20needed%20a%20quick%20edit%20on%20a%20design%20or%20a%20billboard%2C%20I%20could%20call%20in%20a%20favor%20to%20a%20designer%2C%20and%20they'd%20be%20willing%20to%20work%20with%20me%20on%20it%20on%20a%20tight%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompanies%20need%20personality%20hires%20to%20build%20their%20company%20culture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20that%20take%20pride%20in%20having%20%26quot%3Bdisruptive%26quot%3B%20and%20different%20work%20cultures%20need%20personality%20hires%20because%20otherwise%2C%20who's%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-company-culture-companies-comparably-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20that%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20controversial%20to%20say%2C%20but%20employees%20without%20outgoing%20personalities%20aren't%20going%20to%20build%20your%20company%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20non-personality%20hires%20aren't%20as%20fun%20at%20parties%20and%20don't%20provide%20office%20gossip.%20For%20Gen%20Zs%20and%20millennials%2C%20there%20are%20other%20motivators%20for%20going%20to%20work%20than%20just%20doing%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonality%20hires%20can%20also%20help%20companies%20attract%20good%20talent%20by%20providing%20the%20energy%20that%20makes%20other%20people%20want%20to%20come%20work%20at%20your%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222140%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20Bennett%20smiles%20at%20the%20camera.%20In%20front%20of%20him%20is%20a%20name%20plate%20that%20reads%20%26quot%3BDaniel%20Bennett%2C%20Director%20of%20Vibe%20Checks.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661593dc3f923f7dab0601a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222618%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPersonality%20hires%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20building%20company%20culture%2C%20Bennett%20says.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Bennett%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERelationship-building%20is%20extremely%20important%20in%20industries%20such%20as%20entertainment%2C%20sales%2C%20and%20consulting.%20Making%20money%20is%20often%20dependent%20on%20people%20having%20a%20mutual%20likeness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20industries%2C%20personality%20hires%20could%20bring%20more%20value%20than%20employees%20who%20just%20do%20the%20actual%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAs%20a%20boss%2C%20I%20try%20to%20hire%20people%20with%20good%20personalities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20years%20at%20TBWA%5C%5CChiat%5C%5CDay%2C%20I%20quit%20and%20went%20on%20to%20launch%20DX%20Creative%2C%20a%20social%20agency%20helping%20artists%2C%20celebrities%2C%20and%20brands%20with%20short-form%20content%20and%20consulting%2C%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I'm%20considering%20who%20to%20bring%20onto%20my%20team%2C%20I'm%20way%20more%20likely%20to%20extend%20an%20offer%20to%20someone%20if%20I%20like%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20we%20work%20directly%20with%20talent%20and%20celebrities%2C%20we%20need%20people%20who%20can%20be%20friends%20with%20them.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20travel%20involved%2C%20so%20imagine%20traveling%20with%20someone%20that%20you%20don't%20like.%20That%20would%20piss%20people%20off%2C%20so%20we%20need%20people%20who%20will%20vibe%20with%20the%20artist%20they're%20working%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20look%20for%20people%20with%20good%20personalities%20who%20either%20can%20be%20taught%20in%20a%20very%20short%20time%20or%20have%20the%20experience%20we%20can%20mold%20into%20what%20we%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20being%20a%20personality%20hire%20doesn't%20mean%20you're%20bad%20at%20your%20job%3B%20it%20just%20means%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fagreeable-employees-standing-out-more-in-the-workplace-since-pandemic-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersonality%20helped%20you%20get%20hired%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonality-hires-are-important-to-company-culture-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712740201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661591173f923f7dab060010%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonality-hires-are-important-to-company-culture-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20self-proclaimed%20%26quot%3Bpersonality%20hire%26quot%3B%20explains%20how%20he%20and%20his%20fellow%20personality%20hires%20add%20value%20to%20the%20workplace.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jane.zhang%40insider.com%20(Jane%20Zhang)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2