0a%20break%20when%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20C%20Harris%2C%20an%20incoming%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20Journalism%20and%20Creative%20Media%20department%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alabama%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20in%20reality%2C%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%20really%20seems%20to%20do%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20he's%20in%20the%20top%20150%20most%20successful%20YouTubers%20of%20all%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20McLoughlin.%20But%20even%20at%20that%20level%2C%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bno%20protections%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYouTube%20doesn't%20really%20care%20about%20your%20mental%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20you%20to%20keep%20making%20videos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20future%20of%20YouTube%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcLoughlin%20seemed%20to%20air%20some%20frustrations%20about%20what%20YouTube%20has%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgamerant.com%2Fjacksepticeye-mrbeast-twitter-youtube-drama-criticism-explained%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elast%20September%20during%20a%20lie%20detector%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20he%20was%20asked%20his%20opinion%20on%20MrBeast%20%E2%80%94%20the%20platform's%20biggest%20creator%20with%20250%20million%20subs.%20When%20asked%20if%20he%20liked%20his%20fellow%20YouTuber%2C%20McLoughlin%20said%20%26quot%3Bno.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20spoke%20behind%20the%20scenes%20and%20settled%20things.%20But%20in%20hindsight%2C%20McLoughlin's%20opinion%20seems%20to%20stem%20from%20the%20pressure%20YouTubers%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20future%20seems%20to%20be%20fast%20approaching%20where%20MrBeast's%20ridiculously%20high-budget%20content%20monopolizes%20YouTube%20views.%20There%20are%20also%20fears%20about%20how%20AI%20content%20will%20harvest%20the%20rest%20of%20people's%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcLoughlin's%20was%20one%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bold%20guard%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byelling%2