new%20limits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20cracking%20down%20on%20toxic%20%26quot%3Bforever%20chemicals%26quot%3B%20that%20are%20widespread%20in%20America's%20tap%20water%2C%20food%2C%20and%20household%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20EPA%20on%20Wednesday%20finalized%20the%20first-ever%20limits%20on%20levels%20of%20PFAS%20in%20drinking%20water%2C%20putting%20the%20chemicals%20in%20the%20same%20class%20of%20other%20well-known%20pollutants%20like%20lead%2C%20arsenic%2C%20and%20nitrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPFAS%20are%20called%20%26quot%3Bforever%20chemicals%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20don't%20biodegrade%20and%20instead%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaccumulate%20in%20the%20environment%20and%20our%20bodies%20over%20time%2C%20creating%20a%20hazard%20to%20human%20health.%20Peer-reviewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fpfas%2Four-current-understanding-human-health-and-environmental-risks-pfas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudies%20have%20linked%3C%2Fa%3E%20them%20to%20some%20cancers%2C%20decreased%20fertility%2C%20reduced%20vaccine%20response%2C%20high%20cholesterol%2C%20and%20developmental%20delays%20in%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20easily%20the%20most%20consequential%20and%20difficult%20decision%20to%20protect%20drinking%20water%20in%20the%20past%2030%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Ken%20Cook%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Environmental%20Working%20Group%2C%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20watchdog%20group%20started%20researching%20PFAS%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20ago%20and%20found%20PFAS%20everywhere%20they%20tested%2C%20including%20in%20umbilical%20cord%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chemicals%20were%20originally%20developed%20in%20the%201940s%20to%20make%20non-stick%20cookware%2C%20and%20then%20exploded%20in%20use%20in%20clothing%2C%20carpets%2C%20food%20packaging%2C%20and%20firefighting%20foam%20used%20by%20airports%20and%20military%20bases%20to%20put%20out%20jet-fuel%20fires.%20Companies%20that%20make%20PFAS%20also%20dumped%20the%20chemical%20into%20waterways%2C%20landfills%2C%20and%20unlined%20pits%20in%20states%20like%20North%20Carolina%20and%20Minnesota.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEPA%20Administrator%20Michael%20Regan%20is%20announcing%20the%20new%20limits%20in%20drinking%20water%20in%20Fayetteville%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20where%20residents%20in%202017%20learned%20a%20river%20was%20heavily%20contaminated%20with%20PFAS%20pollution%20from%20a%20manufacturing%20plant%20owned%20by%20Chemours%2C%20and%20DuPont%20before%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20action%20will%20prevent%20thousands%20of%20deaths%20and%20reduce%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20serious%20illnesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Regan%20told%20reporters%2C%20citing%20EPA%20estimates%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20drinking%20water%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20thousands%20of%20different%20types%20of%20PFAS%20manufactured%20today.%20The%20EPA%20is%20regulating%20six%20of%20them%20based%20on%20research%20linking%20them%20to%20harm%20and%20showing%20they%20are%20prevalent%20in%20drinking%20water%2C%20David%20Andrews%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20investigations%20and%20senior%20scientists%20at%20EWG%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20include%20PFOA%20and%20PFOS%20that%20persist%20in%20waterways%20and%20the%20environment%2C%20despite%20being%20phased%20out%20of%20production%20in%20the%20US%20since%20the%202000s.%20The%20EPA%20said%20these%20two%20chemicals%20effectively%20aren't%20safe%20at%20any%20level%2C%20but%20the%20lowest%20level%20modern%20labs%20can%20detect%20in%20drinking%20water%20is%204%20parts%20per%20trillion%20%E2%80%94%20the%20limit%20the%20agency%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20limit%20for%20several%20other%20chemicals%20is%2010%20parts%20per%20trillion.%20EPA%20also%20set%20limits%20for%20mixtures%20of%20two%20or%20more%20PFAS%20chemicals%2C%20because%20research%20shows%20they%20may%20have%20combined%20health%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStates%20and%20local%20water%20officials%20will%20have%20five%20years%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20new%20limits%3A%20Three%20to%20test%20PFAS%20levels%3B%20and%20if%20they%20exceed%20the%20federal%20limits%2C%20another%20two%20years%20to%20install%20technology%20that%20cleans%20up%20the%20water.%20The%20administration%20is%20making%20%241%20billion%20available%20in%20grants%20for%20public%20water%20systems%20and%20private%20well%20owners%20to%20install%20treatment%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20administration%20officials%20said%20they%20expect%20up%20to%2010%25%20of%20the%2066%2C000%20water%20systems%20in%20the%20US%20will%20have%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20comply.%20That%20means%20the%20vast%20majority%20won't%20detect%20PFAS%20levels%20beyond%20the%20new%20limits.%20But%20this%20is%20just%20an%20estimate%2C%20they%20added.%20The%20first%20three%20years%20of%20sampling%20will%20indicate%20the%20real%20scope%20of%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20technology%20is%20there%2C%20especially%20to%20clean%20up%20drinking%20water%2C%20to%20filter%20these%20compounds%20out%20of%20the%20water.%20So%20it%20becomes%20a%20question%20of%20cost%20and%20political%20feasibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrews%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20agency%20has%20known%20about%20the%20harms%20that%20these%20chemicals%20can%20cause%20for%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BFor%20too%20long%2C%20many%20people%20across%20the%20country%20have%20had%20been%20drinking%20contaminated%20water%20levels%20that%20likely%20impact%20health.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20a%20broader%20%249%20billion%20PFAS%20strategy%20that%20goes%20beyond%20drinking%20water%2C%20including%20military%20bases%2C%20airports%2C%20and%20food%20packaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Fcfsan-constituent-updates%2Ffda-announces-pfas-used-grease-proofing-agents-food-packaging-no-longer-being-sold-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20February%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20paper%20food%20packaging%20%E2%80%94%20like%20fast-food%20wrappers%2C%20microwave%20popcorn%20bags%2C%20and%20take-out%20pizza%20boxes%20%E2%80%94%20is%20no%20longer%20being%20made%20with%20certain%20kinds%20of%20grease-proofing%20PFAS.%20The%20voluntary%20phase-out%20eliminated%20the%20main%20source%20of%20exposure%20from%20our%20diets%2C%20the%20agency%20said.%20Still%2C%20there%20are%20lingering%20stocks%20of%20packaging%20that%20contain%20PFAS%20that%20could%20take%20months%20to%20be%20exhausted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20scientists%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20these%20are%20important%20steps%2C%20they%20aren't%20enough%20to%20control%20PFAS%20contamination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20better%20than%20no%20regulation%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20just%20a%20Band%20Aid%20solution%20to%20the%20entire%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Carmen%20Messer%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20reproductive%20environmental%20epidemiology%20at%20Harvard's%20TH%20Chan%20School%20of%20Public%20Health%2C%20who%20studies%20PFAS%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20regulate%20the%20entire%20class%20of%20chemicals%20and%20stop%20companies%20from%20manufacturing%20them%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20rather%20than%20try%20to%20regulate%20how%20much%20is%20in%20our%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepa-hazardous-forever-chemicals-drinking-water-limits-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712739662000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F640fabe7f724e7001800d883%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepa-hazardous-forever-chemicals-drinking-water-limits-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Peer-reviewed%20studies%20have%20linked%20PFAS%20to%20some%20cancers%2C%20decreased%20fertility%2C%20high%20cholesterol%2C%20and%20developmental%2