%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227243%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20Ek%20wearing%20sunglasses%20and%20holding%20a%20microphone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654aaf6ab788914e555213e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224901%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniel%20Ek.%3Cp%3EDave%20Benett%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20companies%2C%20Spotify%20over-hired%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20It%20nearly%20doubled%20its%20head%20count%20between%202019%20and%202022.%20Then%2C%20last%20year%2C%20it%20cut%202%2C300%20jobs%20through%20three%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%20in%20January%2C%20June%2C%20and%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20think%20Spotify%20is%20spending%20too%20much%20on%20parties%20and%20events%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20company%20is%20laying%20off%20thousands%20of%20people%20and%20looking%20to%20cut%20more%20costs.%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%2014%20current%20and%20former%20workers%20who%20shared%20details%20of%20what%20they%20described%20as%20poorly%20timed%2C%20extravagant%20parties.%20They%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20discussing%20sensitive%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20is%20in%20the%20entertainment%20business%2C%20so%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20extravagant%20events%20are%20part%20of%20the%20deal.%20But%20these%20employees%20said%20event%20spending%20had%20gone%20too%20far%2C%20given%20the%20company's%20broader%20efforts%20at%20frugality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20surprising%20to%20me%20that%20they%20stated%20they're%20on%20a%20cost-cutting%20drive%20but%20then%20continued%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20staffer%20told%20BI.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EKeep%20Wrapping%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Spotify%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20would%20continue%20events%20such%20as%20Wrapped%2C%20Stockholm%20Intro%20Days%2C%20and%20the%20Best%20New%20Artist%20Grammy%20party.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20these%20were%20%26quot%3Bkey%20to%20promoting%20artists%2C%20engaging%20listeners%2C%20encouraging%20collaboration%20amongst%20employees%2C%20and%20highlighting%20our%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BSpotify%20is%20a%20global%20company%20dedicated%20to%20celebrating%20creators%2C%20fostering%20a%20collaborative%20employee%20culture%2C%20and%20recognising%20team%20achievements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20declined%20to%20comment%20when%20BI%20asked%20how%20much%20it%20spent%20on%20parties%20and%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpotifest%202023%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpotifest%2C%20a%20music%20festival%20just%20for%20Spotify%20staff%2C%20stands%20out%20in%20employees'%20minds%20as%20an%20example%20of%20lavish%20spending.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20Spotifest%20took%20place%20in%20August.%20Hundreds%20of%20employees%20gathered%20at%20The%20Brooklyn%20Mirage%20in%20New%20York%20for%20the%20event.%20Laser%20lights%20beamed%20onto%20attendees'%20faces%20in%20the%20outdoor%20courtyard%20as%20the%20headliners%20Diplo%20and%20T-Pain%20performed%20on%20a%20huge%20stage.%20Elsewhere%2C%20acrobats%20performed%2C%20drag%20performers%20danced%2C%20and%20beer%20was%20served%20out%20of%20backpack%20kegs%2C%20according%20to%20people%20in%20attendance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20was%20lit%20up%20by%20orange%20and%20blue%20spotlights%2C%20with%20one%20wall%20lined%20by%20a%20bar%20serving%20drinks%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DHlzpy7o6rZw%26t%3D1s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EYouTube%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20video%20from%20the%20event%20shows.%20Attractions%20included%20a%20barbershop%2C%20photo%20booths%2C%20music-listening%20stations%2C%20a%20series%20of%20games%2C%20and%20a%20temporary-tattoo%20studio%20that%20branded%20employees%20with%20Spotify's%20logo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConcerns%20shrugged%20off%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20before%20Spotifest%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.spotify.com%2F2023-06-05%2Fan-update-on-changes-to-spotifys-podcast-business-june-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecut%20200%20jobs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%2C%20during%20the%20first%20round%20of%20cuts%2C%20Ek%20told%20employees%20in%20a%20memo%20that%20the%20company%20needed%20to%20%26quot%3Bcontrol%20costs%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20had%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Bconsiderable%20effort%20to%20rein-in%20costs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20one%20worker%20said%20Spotifest%20was%20a%20good%20way%20to%20boost%20employee%20morale%2C%20another%20said%20the%20event%20was%20poorly%20timed%20once%20layoffs%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20employee%20who%20dealt%20with%20budgets%20said%20they%20attempted%20to%20raise%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20company%20needing%20to%20be%20better%20with%20spending%2C%20but%20their%20concerns%20were%20shrugged%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntro%20Days%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221620%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Employees%20sitting%20around%20tables%20in%20a%20colorful%20office%20space.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c645207dde867025c065ba9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmployees%20in%20a%20meeting%20at%20Spotify's%20headquarters%20in%20Stockholm%20in%20March%202014.%3Cp%3EMelanie%20Stetson%20Freeman%2FThe%20Christian%20Science%20Monitor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify's%20events%20largely%20fall%20into%20two%20categories.%20There%20are%20parties%20and%20events%20that%20are%20open%20to%20the%20public%2C%20which%20essentially%20function%20as%20brand%20marketing.%20Then%20there%20are%20employee-only%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20it's%20a%20team%20party%2C%20Grammys%20party%2C%20Christmas%20party%2C%20branded%20parties%2C%20or%20extra%20parties%20that%20are%20relatively%20under%20the%20wraps%2C%20there's%20certainly%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20being%20thrown%20at%20parties%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20headquartered%20in%20Stockholm%2C%20and%20it%20sends%20many%20new%20hires%20there%20for%20%26quot%3BIntro%20Days%2C%26quot%3B%20during%20which%20they%20network%2C%20hear%20from%20speakers%2C%20and%20get%20up%20to%20speed%20on%20Spotify%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20employee%20described%20it%20as%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bspending%20tons%20of%20money%20flying%20people%20to%20Sweden%20to%20drink%20the%20Kool-Aid.%26quot%3B%20Several%20people%20who%20went%20on%20the%20trips%20told%20BI%20the%20company%20would%20put%20employees%20up%20in%20a%20hotel%20for%20three%20to%20five%20days%20and%20cover%20all%20their%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20literally%20just%20sit%20in%20a%20room%20and%20listen%20to%20executives%20talk%20back-to-back%20for%20three%20days%2C%20and%20then%20there's%20a%20party%20at%20the%20end%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20such%20a%20stupid%20waste%20of%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20worker%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20questioned%20executive%20leadership's%20decision-making%20and%20where%20they%20spend%20money%2C%20and%20I%20think%20Intro%20Days%20are%20a%20good%20example.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20person%20said%20it%20showed%20poor%20leadership%20for%20Spotify%20to%20continue%20spending%20on%20parties%20and%20trips%20despite%20economic%20headwinds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeyond%20music%20streaming%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alicia%20Keys%20and%20Daniel%20Ek%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20a%20wall%20made%20to%20look%20like%20a%20giant%20bookshelf.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66105edc16bde8d4ead642e5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222359%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlicia%20Keys%20and%20Daniel%20Ek%20at%20The%20Future%20of%20Audiobooks%20Event%20with%20Spotify%202023%20in%20New%20York%20City%20in%20October.%3Cp%3ENoam%20Galai%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20this%20lavish%20event%20spending%20is%20focused%20on%20solving%20a%20problem%20that%20has%20loomed%20over%20Spotify%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tough%20economics%20of%20the%20music-streaming%20business%20mean%20Spotify%20pays%20out%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20230329205213%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Floudandclear.byspotify.com%2F%23box-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E70%25%20of%20its%20revenue%20to%20music%20rights%20holders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20company%20blog%20from%20early%202023.%20As%20more%20music%20is%20streamed%20on%20the%20service%2C%20these%20payouts%20generally%20increase%20at%20a%20similar%20rate.%20So%20as%20the%20company%20grows%2C%20expenses%20climb%2C%20too.%20This%20has%20been%20a%20concern%20for%20investors%20who%20prefer%20software%20business%20models%20that%20typically%20make%20a%20lot%20more%20money%20as%20sales%20rise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20for%20Spotify%20to%20tackle%20this%20challenge%20is%20to%20expand%20beyond%20music%20streaming%20and%20embrace%20other%20businesses%20with%20more%20scalable%20economics%2C%20such%20as%20podcasts%2C%20audiobooks%2C%20and%20concert%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20spent%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20on%20podcasts%20and%20went%20on%20an%20acquisition%20spree%20in%202019%20through%20buying%20three%20podcast%20studios%20totaling%20%24375%20million.%20Spotify%20says%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.spotify.com%2Fus%2Fpodcasters%2Farticle%2Funderstanding-rpm-how-you-earn-money-with-ads%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etakes%20a%2050%25%20commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20revenue%20from%20ads%20on%20podcasts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20also%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22ht