20seeds%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20their%20sovereignty%20over%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%20Since%20then%2C%20Neelam%E2%80%99s%20mission%20has%20been%20to%20conserve%20decade-old%20seeds%20for%20future%20generations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacked%20by%20the%20traditional%20wisdom%20imparted%20by%20his%20father%20and%20the%20elderly%20in%20the%20village%2C%20he%20set%20out%20in%20search%20of%20these%20heirloom%20treasures.%20In%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20Neelam%20has%20conserved%20nearly%20800%20varieties%20of%20vegetables%20like%20tomatoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20capsicum%2C%20basil%2C%20and%20200%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331636%2Fassam-farmer-starts-rice-library-grows-preserves-indigenous-rice-varieties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evarieties%20of%20rice%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Cem%3Emadhuri%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Enanyya%20rice%2C%20sticky%20gum%20rice%2C%20black%20rice%2C%20soft%20rice%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejoha.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20seeds%20have%20their%20own%20identity%20in%20terms%20of%20taste%2C%20colour%2C%20and%20shape.%20They%20are%20adaptable%20to%20the%20diverse%20Indian%20climatic%20zones.%20In%20one%20way%2C%20they%20are%20more%20resilient%20than%20hybrid%20seeds%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHybrid%20vs%20heirloom%20seeds%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Forganic-farming-1-1712236952.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neelam%20says%20he%20wanted%20the%20local%20farmers%20in%20his%20region%20to%20wholeheartedly%20adopt%20and%20switch%20to%20heirloom%20seeds.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F